(41, 1, 26, 42, 9, 42, 42, 'torn him, and cried with a loud voice', 'Connection of Unclean Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the action of an unclean spirit causing distress to a person. In Mark, the spirit ''tore'' the individual, while in Luke, the devil ''threw him down, and tare him.'' This connection highlights the similar manifestations of demonic influence in both accounts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
