(41, 1, 27, 40, 15, 31, 31, 'What new doctrine is this?', 'Authority and Wonder in Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the amazement of the crowd at miraculous acts. In Mark, the authority of Jesus over unclean spirits leads to astonishment, while in Matthew, the healing of various ailments causes the multitude to glorify God. This connection highlights the theme of divine authority eliciting wonder.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
