(41, 1, 27, 42, 9, 1, 1, 'with authority commandeth he even the unclean spirits', 'Authority Over Unclean Spirits', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority in both passages. In Mark, Jesus commands unclean spirits with authority, while in Luke, he empowers his disciples with similar authority over devils.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 27, 40, 9, 33, 33, 'with authority commandeth he even the unclean spirits', 'Authority Over Unclean Spirits', 'Both passages emphasize the authority Jesus has over unclean spirits, leading to amazement among the people. In Mark, the crowd questions the new doctrine and authority, while in Matthew, the multitudes marvel at the miraculous event.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 27, 42, 4, 36, 36, 'with authority commandeth he even the unclean spirits', 'Authority Over Unclean Spirits', 'Both passages emphasize the authority Jesus has over unclean spirits, leading to amazement among the people. The similar phrasing regarding his command reflects a shared theme of his power in exorcism.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 27, 41, 10, 24, 24, 'they were all amazed', 'Authority and Astonishment', 'Both passages emphasize the astonishment of the people and disciples at Jesus'' teachings. The amazement in Mark 1:27 reflects a response to His authority, while Mark 10:24 shows the disciples'' astonishment at His challenging words about wealth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
